Last week I went to @gregisenberg's Offline Mode Mastermind in Florida. 
Two days in a mansion with 30 of the sharpest founders, builders, and creators I've ever been in a room with. 
And it reminded me of something most internet entrepreneurs forget: 
While you sure CAN build alone.  You CANNOT grow alone. 
Here's what I took away: 
1️⃣ There's a Loneliness Tax to building solo and most of us are paying it without realizing.
 • Get in a room with other founders and watch how fast the fog clears. 
2️⃣ The biggest skill in business is pattern recognition and it sharpens around other founders solving real problems.

• You can't develop that scrolling Twitter. You develop it by understanding trends and hearing how others are navigating the same walls you're hitting. 
3️⃣ Your ideas need cross-pollination. Isolation is where great ideas go to die.

• One conversation with the right person will unlock what months behind a screen never will. 
4️⃣ Real human connection isn't a nice-to-have. It's a force multiplier.

• The relationships you build in rooms like this will outperform any course or YouTube video you watch. 
The @ideabrowserteam built something special with Offline Mode. 
No fluff.  No posturing.  Just founders helping founders IRL. 
It wasn't a break from work. It was the highest-leverage work I did all month. 
If you get the chance to be in a room like that, “go to the thing.” 
The next time Greg and the LateCheckout team do an event, don’t sleep on it. 
I'm Martin DeSouza

